pdc@dcs.ed.ac.uk (Paul Crowley) writes:
: At the moment, I can't think how to define the problem precisely enough
: to prove that spoofing is impossible.  Here's what I can prove: if Alice
: and Bob want to talk, and I know everything Bob knows, and I can spoof
: the channel, I can make it impossible for Alice to tell me from Bob.  I
: let Bob's messages go through unscathed, but I put a message of my own
: randomly before or after with all the non-cryptographic information the
: same and all the cryptographic information from my sources rather than
: his.  There is now no way for Alice to tell us apart; we are the same.

What if I can say something to Alice that the spoof *must* substitute
something arbitrary for (in my voice at best?)  I've gotten this far with
the problem.

